               <p>THIRD AND FOURTH COUNTS, the same as the two former, only calling the forged instrument a certain order for payment of money, instead of a certain warrant for payment of money.</p>
               <p>FIFTH AND SIXTH COUNTS, for feloniously offering a certain false, forged, and counterfeit warrant, for payment of money; well knowing it to be false, forged, and counterfeited, with a like intention.</p>
               <p>SEVENTH AND EIGHTH COUNTS, the same as the fifth and sixth, only calling the forged instrument a false, forged, and counterfeited order, for payment of money, instead of a certain warrant for payment of money.</p>
               <p>FOUR OTHER COUNTS, like the four last, only for feloniously disposing of and putting away, instead of offering, with a like intention.</p>
